<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
  <div class="section-intro mb-10">
    <div class="eyebrow">Featured talk</div>
    <h2>A practical model for agentic engineering.</h2>
  </div>

  <article class="talk-feature">
    <div class="talk-feature-meta">
      <span class="talk-status talk-status-presented">Presented</span>
      <span>Advanced · AI-assisted development</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="pillar-label">Engineering Triad</p>
      <h2>The Agentic Developer</h2>
      <p class="talk-subtitle">Stop with Vibe Coding and Master the Engineering Triad</p>
      <p class="talk-alternate-title">Also presented as <strong>The Agentic Engineer: Making Implicit Engineering Explicit</strong>. These are two titles for the same session.</p>
      <p>Generated code is not delivered work. This talk introduces a practical model for making agent contributions reliable, observable, and safe by making three parts of engineering explicit: intent, context, and execution.</p>
      <p>Using a password-reset flow as a running example, the session moves from vague prompting to durable specifications, BDD scenarios, repository rules, focused agent roles, validation gates, and human acceptance.</p>
      <p class="topic-outcome">Audience takeaway: when execution becomes cheap, clarity becomes the engineering bottleneck. Do not only fix an agent's output; improve the environment that produced it.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>

